**Depth follows evidence:** start with a trigger-aimed probe. Rotate after a
genuinely cold deterministic result; go deep when the trigger is variable or a
run shows progress toward the predicted failure. Coverage of more precise
hypotheses finds more bugs than repeating nearby inputs with no new evidence.
